# NAME
. git - the stupid content tracker 🚀

# SYNOPSIS
$ git [--version] [--help] [-C <path>] [-c <name>=<value>]
$     [--exec-path[=<path>]] [--html-path] [--man-path] [--info-path]
$     [-p | --paginate | -P | --no-pager] [--no-replace-objects] [--bare]
$     [--git-dir=<path>] [--work-tree=<path>] [--namespace=<name>]
$     [--config-env=<name>=<envvar>] <command> [<args>]

# DESCRIPTION
. **Git** is a fast, scalable, distributed revision control system with an
 unusually rich command set that provides both high-level operations
 and full access to internals. 🛠️

. This guide is designed to test the **Advanced Layout Engine**. It contains
 various complex tokens to verify UTF-8 safety, tiered breakpoints, and
 style persistence.

# ADVANCED WRAPPING TEST
## Deep Paths & URLs
. The engine should intelligently wrap long technical strings at logical
 break points like slashes or dots:
. `/data/data/com.termux/files/home/works/gig/src/layout/wrap.c`
. `https://github.com/google/gemini-cli/blob/main/src/pager/render.c#L123`

## Bracket Awareness
. Technical text often contains nested groupings. The engine should prioritize
 breaking *before* an opening bracket to keep parameters grouped:
. `func([long_parameter_name], {nested_config_object: "value"}, <placeholder>)`

## Style Persistence
. **This paragraph starts bold and contains a `Sage Green Command` and a
 <Terracotta Argument> to ensure that styles do not "bleed" or get lost
 across the many line breaks that occur in a narrow viewport.**

# RESPONSIVE TABLES
| Section | Flag | Description & Long Content
| :--- | :--- | :---
| Core | `--bare` | Treat the repository as a bare repository. It does not have a working directory.
| Config | `-c <n>=<v>` | Pass a configuration parameter to the command. Example: `git -c core.editor=vim commit`.
| Search | `--grep` | **Note**: Searches for patterns in the commit log message. It is very useful for finding specific changes.

# TECHNICAL BLOCKS
## Literal Configuration (Non-Wrapping)
! # This block tests smart truncation for extremely long literal lines:
! [remote "origin"]
!     url = https://very-long-and-nested-subdomain.example.com/path/to/repo/that/is/deeply/nested/and/should/be/truncated.git
!     fetch = +refs/heads/*:refs/remotes/origin/*

# NOTES
> **WARNING**: Git is a powerful tool. Commands like `rm -rf` or
> `reset --hard` can result in permanent data loss if not used
> with extreme caution. (POSIX compliance is mandatory: π ≈ 3.14159).

. For more information, visit the official site at "https://git-scm.com".
